      "message": "Note on changes since PS5: Previously if a texture was of type GL_TEXTURE_EXTERNAL we would fail when we called GrGpu::writePixels(). Now we post a task, so the failure gets delayed to task execution and GrSurfaceContext::writePixels would returning true. This was the source of the failure on PS 5 (expected writePixels to fail). Now I made GrTexture and GrTextureProxy mark a texture as \"read only\" (we never want to or can really write to EXTERNAL textures) so now writePixels fails earlier do to GrCaps::surfaceSupportsWritePixels() and the test passes.\n\nI should also mentioned the changes to GrResourceCache are no-ops. I noticed we were passing caps and storing the prefersVRAMUseOverFlushes value but never actually using it in the class.",
